An '''Emperor's Eye''' was an exalted level of [[Dark side adept/Legends|Dark Side Adept]] loyal to [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. It was higher in rank than the [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]].

==History==
Their counterparts included the [[Emperor's Reach]], [[Emperor's Voice (Galactic Empire)|Emperor's Voice]], and the [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hands]]. The "Eyes" possessed a particular propensity for [[Farsight/Legends|seeing]] into [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and the future. Only two Eyes ever existed, [[Merili]] and [[Triclops]]. Palpatine entrusted the duty of training one of these two to the [[Prophets of the Dark Side]].<ref name="Evil">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref>

{{Imp-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The group was first mentioned in ''Star Wars: TIE Fighter'', where the player character, [[Maarek Stele/Legends|Maarek Stele]], was made into an Emperor's Eye by the Secret Order of the Emperor after completing an indeterminant amount of missions. Despite this, however, Stele's position as such is questionable due to other sources stating there weren't any other Emperor's eyes outside of Merili and Triclops.

